Key Match Events: Netherlands beat Nepal by six wickets.
Nepal were bowled out for 106 in 19.2 overs.
Netherlands chased down the target in 18.4 overs, scoring 109-4.
Max O'Dowd scored an unbeaten 54 runs.
Sandeep Lamichhane took 3 wickets for 20 runs.
Rohit Paudel scored 35 runs for Nepal.
Logan van Beek took 3 wickets for 18 runs.
Post-Match Reflections: Netherlands captain Scott Edwards admitted that winning the toss helped them get a read on the wicket and praised the bowlers for their performance.
Nepal captain Rohit Paudel reflected on the challenging overhead conditions and acknowledged that the batting unit could have done better.
Paudel also mentioned the lack of partnerships and the impact of dropped catches on the outcome of the match.
Tim Pringle, named Player of the Match, highlighted the importance of speed and changing pace as a spinner.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The conditions at the start of the match were overcast, favoring seam bowlers, while it was sunny during the Netherlands' chase.
The Nepal-heavy crowd in Dallas showed great support and appreciation for both teams despite the loss.
